SEMDL Help Topic: grammar

- Root form: `ssd <subcommand> ...`
- Help form: `ssd help [topic] [--format semdl]`
- Targeted reference help: `ssd help reference [subcommand] [--format semdl]`
- Targeted recipe help: `ssd help recipes [topic] [--format semdl]`
- Global help alias: `ssd --help [--format semdl]`
- Subcommand help alias: `ssd <subcommand> --help [--format semdl]`

Topic targeting:
- `overview`, `toc`, `grammar`, `samples`, and `troubleshooting` do not accept a trailing target
- `reference` accepts a `<subcommand>` target
- `recipes` accepts a `<topic>` target

Key syntax forms:
- `ssd check <file>`
- `ssd search <query.ssq> <file>...`
- `ssd extract --out <output.ssd> <input>...`
- `ssd similarity <id> <id> <file>`
- `ssd explain <id> <file>`
- `ssd add <kind> <file> [field=value ...] [--stdout|--out <file> [--dry-run]|--target sidecar|--dry-run]`
- `ssd set <selector> <value-or-field> ... <file>`
- `ssd remove <selector> <file>`
- `ssd annotate <selector> <kind> <text> ... <file>`
- `ssd split <input.ssd> [--dry-run]`
- `ssd merge <input.ssd> [--stdout|--dry-run|--out <file> [--dry-run]] [--prefer-source inline|sidecar] [--warn-on-conflict] [--fail-on-conflict]`
- `ssd normalize <input.ssd> [--stdout|--dry-run [--format inline|sidecar]|--out <file> [--format inline|sidecar] [--dry-run]]`
- `ssd help grammar --format semdl`

Selectors:
- `id:<id>`
- `type:<kind>`
- `path:<id>.<field>`
- `meta:<id>.<field>`
- `doc:self`
- Use `path:` for inline `.ssd` structure and `meta:` for sidecar `.ssm` metadata

Value forms:
- text with spaces should be passed as a quoted string
- update-oriented scalar values accept quoted-string, number, boolean, or identifier forms

Common options:
- `--dry-run` previews update-oriented commands
- `--stdout` is currently used by `add`, `merge`, `normalize`, and `extract`
- `normalize --dry-run` and `normalize --out` accept `--format inline|sidecar`; help render keeps separate `--format semdl`
- `annotate` accepts `--target inline|sidecar|auto`; metadata-only `add` still requires `--target sidecar`
- `--allow-multi` and `--cascade` are safety controls on specific update forms; `--prefer-source inline|sidecar`, `--warn-on-conflict`, and `--fail-on-conflict` are currently merge-only trailing options

This topic is the canonical user-facing operational syntax summary.
Use `ssd help reference <subcommand>` or `ssd <subcommand> --help` for command-specific usage details.
Use `--format semdl` for line-preserving SEMDL help output.
For command-specific help, see `ssd help reference <subcommand>`.
